rComments: Lecture slides are informative; material was interesting. Some material does need further clarification. Professor is very responsive however, and really does care in trying to help the students understand!

His teaching is not that bad. It's just, he teaches us too many things in 3 months. The content is amazing and useful if you are really interested in them, if not, it feels like there's no point of learning and memorizing them. He listens to the students really well, and was extremely reliable.

super accomodating prof, adjusts deadlines and replies quickly on piazza and takes feedback well. On the otherhand the Programming Languages course probably has more content than I've ever seen in a course and really needs to be trimmed down

Extremely helpful when students ask questions during or outside of class. The forum for the class was managed consistently and every question got an answer. He listens to the student's individual needs as well as the needs of the class as a whole in order to help us succeed as much as possible. Tests are extremely hard but are curved.

Honestly the most accommodating prof I've had so far in my undergrad. While the assignments are definitely time-consuming and on the tougher side, Jack tries his best to help whenever possible and also provides reasonable extensions.

Great professor, definitely cared about students and material. Labs are difficult but manageable. They are also worth a lot, so put in the effort and you should get all lab marks. Exams were very hard but there was always a "+X" to everyone's grade to makeup for it.
Really cares about the course material and the students
Amazing lectures! Assignments are a bit hard but bonus was given to compensate.

Gives good lectures, replies to emails and postings quickly. He's also very caring for he extended assignment deadlines just for students to have enough time to finish. He releases practice midterm and final WITH TOPIC BREAKDOWN one week earlier than the actual exam so you can have a general sense of what the exam's about and difficulty level.
